  <h1>
   filename_name
  </h1>
  Using this function returns the name part of the indicated file,
  <i>
   with
  </i>
  the extension but
  <i>
   without
  </i>
  the path.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">filename_name(fname);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      fname
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        String
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The file to use.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 String
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">name = filename_name(file_find_first("C:/Games/*.doc", 0));
</code></pre>
  The above code gets the name (as a string) of the first "doc" type file found in the specified directory.
 </body>
</html>